Gauteng Provincial COVID-19 council briefs the media on the status of the fight against the spread of the coronavirus in the province.  JOHANNESBURG - The Gauteng Provincial Government Command Council will give an update on the status of the fight against the spread of the coronavirus in the province. The province has over 7,000 COVID-19 infections with 57 deaths. Gauteng's recoveries stand at 2,825. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.